N:jeo
D:[jeo] Packet-first integrated agent orchestration router. Use when the user wants one front door for plan approval, runtime handoff, browser/UI verification, resume or recovery, and durable `.jeo` task history across Claude Code, Codex CLI, Gemini CLI, or OpenCode. Route spec-first loops to `ralph`, plan review to `plannotator`, runtime-native execution to `omc` / `omx` / `ohmg`, browser verification to `agent-browser`, submit-gated UI review to `agentation`, and trust-posture tuning to `ralphmode`.
G:jeo orchestration annotate ui-review agentui ralph plannotator omc omx ohmg bmad agent-browser agentation multi-agent workflow resume recovery ledger phase-router packet-router cleanup browser-verification ui-feedback submit-gate onsubmit 오케스트레이션 계획 실행 검증 정리 재개

U[5]:
  Use one orchestration front door while keeping runtime-native execution in sibling skills
  Maintain a durable `.jeo` ledger plus resumable machine state across planning, execution, verification, and cleanup
  Resume previous work instead of rebuilding plan/task structure from scratch
  Add browser verification and optional submit-gated UI review when the delivery loop needs it
  Keep honest route-outs to `ralph`, `plannotator`, `omc`, `omx`, `ohmg`, `agent-browser`, `agentation`, and `ralphmode`

S[8]{n,action,details}:
  1,Bootstrap-or-Resume,initialize or recover `.jeo` and machine state with jeo-state-update.py + jeo-project-sync.py
  2,Choose-Packet,classify the request as bootstrap-or-resume / planning-gate / runtime-handoff / verification-loop / annotate-submit-loop / cleanup-and-closeout
  3,Plan-Gate,checkpoint plan state and route plan shaping/review to `ralph` + `plannotator`
  4,Runtime-Handoff,checkpoint execute state and hand approved work to `omc` / `omx` / `ohmg` or truthful `bmad` fallback
  5,Verify,checkpoint verify state and collect QA evidence with `agent-browser` when browser-visible behavior matters
  6,Annotate-Loop,only after explicit submit/onSubmit, route UI annotation processing to `agentation`
  7,Cleanup,complete task summary, queue follow-up work if needed, and run worktree cleanup
  8,Boundary-Check,keep runtime config/hooks in references or sibling skills instead of re-expanding the main skill

R[6]:
  Never enter EXECUTE without plan approval
  Never reopen an unchanged approved plan
  Never process annotations before explicit submit/onSubmit
  Completion requires QA evidence or an explicit skip reason
  Persist durable context in `.jeo/` and resumable machine state before leaving a phase
  JEO is the router and ledger contract, not the owner of runtime internals

E[3]{desc,in,out}:
  "Resume existing workflow","python3 scripts/jeo-state-update.py resume && python3 scripts/jeo-project-sync.py status","Current phase, active task, and ledger status recovered"
  "Cross-platform delivery loop","jeo 'ship analytics dashboard with annotate'","Packet chooses plan/runtime/verify owners, preserves `.jeo`, and routes runtime-specific work honestly"
  "Queue follow-up after QA","python3 scripts/jeo-project-sync.py queue qa-follow-up 'Fix chart legend overlap'","New queued work item added without rebuilding the ledger"
